Congratulations to PLHS Senior Magnus O'Connor who earned the highest possible ACT composite score of 36!

Less than one-half of 1% of all test takers earn the top score. Among U.S. high school graduates in the class of 2019, just 4,879 out of nearly 1.8 million students who took the ACT earned a composite score of 36.

#WeArePLSAS

post_text:
Join our team as a Paraprofessional!
Special Education Paraprofessionals assist students with special needs under the direction of a certified teacher.

Paraprofessionals generally work in both special education and general education classrooms. The Special Education Paraprofessional assists students in daily classroom activities and academics and cares for their physical, social/emotional health and safety, affirming their abilities, and striving to promote dignity in all relationships.

Click the link below to learn more and apply!
https://www.applitrack.com/priorlake/onlineapp/default.aspx

post_text:
Thank you for your patience as we have been preparing our back-to-school plans. PLSAS will start the school year in the Hybrid Learning model for all K-12 students. The Hybrid model is a system that uses a combination of learning at-home and in-person learning at school.

It is important to know that this decision could change before the start of school, based on directives and updated COVID-19 data from the MN Department Health and Scott County. If this were to happen, we will be sure to communicate the change as soon as possible.

Click the link below for important back-to-school information and our PLSAS Ready to Learn plan. We look forward to welcoming students and staff back to school!

https://bit.ly/31Lq5cd

post_text:
Prior Lake High School will NOT be a host site for the National ACT Test on Saturday, June 13, 2020.

ACT was notified at the end of May that school facilities cannot be used for large group testing in Minnesota through the end of June per Commissioner Ricker. We will reevaluate for the July 18 National Test date.

ACT should be notifying all registered families this week.

If you have questions, please contact Beth Fuller: bfuller@priorlake-savage.k12.mn.us

post_text: Our PLSAS community is mourning the loss of former Superintendent, Dr. Sue Ann Gruver who passed away April 28. Dr. Gruver was Superintendent of PLSAS from 2008 until her retirement in 2015. During her time as Superintendent, she was instrumental in bringing new programs to the district including SAGE Academy, La ola del lago Spanish Immersion, MNCAPS, E-STEM and the PLHS FabLab. During her tenure she also opened Redtail Ridge and an addition to PLHS. We will miss her dearly. https://www.startribune.com/obituaries/detail/0000354329/?fullname=sue-ann-(wilkinson)-gruver
shared_text:
STARTRIBUNE.COM
Obituary for Sue Ann (Wilkinson) Gruver
text:
Our PLSAS community is mourning the loss of former Superintendent, Dr. Sue Ann Gruver who passed away April 28. Dr. Gruver was Superintendent of PLSAS from 2008 until her retirement in 2015. During her time as Superintendent, she was instrumental in bringing new programs to the district including SAGE Academy, La ola del lago Spanish Immersion, MNCAPS, E-STEM and the PLHS FabLab. During her tenure she also opened Redtail Ridge and an addition to PLHS. We will miss her dearly. https://www.startribune.com/obituaries/detail/0000354329/?fullname=sue-ann-(wilkinson)-gruver

Tomorrow is National Decision Day— a day of celebration for seniors when they notify the Prior Lake High School guidance office of where to send their final transcript and take a survey about their future plans.

We can't celebrate in person this year, so help us honor our 2020 grads by sharing the story of your journey after high school graduation.

Did you go to college, a career or the Military? Was your path unexpected? Share photos and stories by tagging us (@PLSAS) and using #PLDecisionDay & #Lakers2020

post_text:
Today Governor Tim Walz announced that all MN schools will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year and has ordered Distance Learning to continue for all students.

As much as we were looking forward to having students back in their school buildings at the beginning of May, we know that this decision was made to help keep everyone safe during this COVID-19 pandemic.

We have many details to determine in the next few weeks including how we will commemorate graduation, other summer school, locker clean-outs and more. As decisions are made, we will share them with you.

Please access our website for details. www.priorlake-savage.k12.mn.us/COVID-19

During spring break, PLSAS will not be distributing food, but there are several options for families who need support.

- Food will be available for pick up at the ROCK warehouse (16511 Anna Trail, Suite E, Prior Lake) on Mondays and Wednesdays from 4-7 p.m.

- You may text your needs to (952) 333-4827 and a ROCK volunteer will drop off food to your home.

- Your School Social Worker can connect you to resources in the community.
Find your social worker: https://www.priorlake-savage.k12.mn.us/about-us/departments/social-work

We have also compiled a list of resources on our district’s COVID-19 page: https://www.priorlake-savage.k12.mn.us/covid-19

- Starting March 30 -
Curbside food pickup will resume at WestWood. At that time, we will also begin offering food delivery to families in need.

In response to an executive order from Governor Walz regarding coronavirus (COVID-19), PLSAS will close schools Mon. March 16 through Fri. March 27th to allow more time to plan for the possibility of a period of distance learning after spring break. There will be no student instruction during closure. All employees should report to work March 16 and continue to follow their current work calendar.

Activities, events & practices also canceled during this time period.

We have designed Personalized Flex Learning days and will be working to implement these plans, if necessary.

Spring break remains the same, March 23-27.

Please refer to our website for all COVID-19 communications and additional resources & public health links. https://www.priorlake-savage.k12.mn.us/about-us/coronavirus-virus

post_text:
As an 11-year old in April, Gavin Shaner scored a 33 on the ACT. His score was the same or higher than 98% of recent high school graduates in the US.

As a 12-year-old in June, he scored 1490 on the SAT, which puts him in the 99th percentile among 11th and 12th graders.

He was recognized at a Northwestern University Midwest Academic Talent Search Ceremony in Evanston, Illinois on September 14. He was one of only four 7th graders who received top scores on all six possible categories for these tests, including first place on Evidence-based reading and writing out of 3,097 gifted 7th graders.

He was also recognized at the Minnesota ceremony October 5 and placed first among all of the Minnesota 7th graders on the ACT Composite, SAT Composite and EBRW sections.

#WeArePLSAS

post_text:
It's Farm to School week and schools throughout PLSAS are helping get local corn to lunch trays by participating in corn husking relays!

Some Prior Lake High School students and Student Council members competed for a chance to win a treat from LakerMarketplace.

All contestants received a drink coupon for Lake House Café, and each student on the winning team received a muffin!

#WeArePLSAS #Farm2School
